<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910930-0025</DOCNO><DOCID>910930-0025.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Pancho's Mexican Buffet Inc.:   Chain to Take Charge   Of At Least $8 Million</HL><DATE>09/30/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   PAMX</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>ENTERTAINMENT AND LEISURE (ENT)RESTAURANTS, FAST-FOOD, CATERING (RES)</IN><NS>EARNINGS PROJECTIONS (ERP)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Pancho's Mexican Buffet Inc., Fort Worth, Texas, said itexpects to take a pretax charge of $8 million to $9 millionfor writing down the value of certain restaurants, closing asmany as four restaurants and providing reserves for workers'compensation insurance.   The operator of 66 Mexican restaurants, said the netcharge of about $1.30 a share, is expected to result in a netloss for the fiscal year ending today.</LP><TEXT>   Hollis Taylor, president and chief executive officer, saidthe company plans to create a $3.5 million reserve forpossible workers' compensation claims for past years to avoidtaking charges over the next several years. It changed itscoverage this year, so it needs to reserve only for previousyears. The company also plans to write down its investmentsin underperforming restaurants.   In the fourth quarter last year, Pancho's had net incomeof $910,000, or 21 cents a share, on sales of $19.3 million.</TEXT></DOC>